# iOS platform

## Source set

- `composeApp/src/iosMain/kotlin/app/mymultiverse/kmp/`
- Shared UI in `commonMain` — iosMain is platform adapters only.

## expect/actual in this project

| Feature | iosMain location |
|---------|------------------|
| Auth deeplink | `data/supabase/AuthDeeplinkHandler.ios.kt` |
| Language | `domain/manager/IOSLanguageManager.kt` |
| Haptics | `presentation/platform/JourneyHaptics.ios.kt` (no-op today) |
| Push token | `data/platform/` APNs registration |
| Personal export | `data/platform/` |

## UIKit & interop

- Use `platform.UIKit.*` when native UI is required.
- `@ObjCName` on public APIs exposed to Swift for clean names.
- Prefer Compose Multiplatform for all screens — no duplicate SwiftUI flows unless unavoidable.

## Build & CI

- iOS compile **not** in default CI (cost); verify locally or manual workflow dispatch.
- `./gradlew :composeApp:compileKotlinIosSimulatorArm64`
- Xcode project: `iosApp/` — embeds Compose framework from KMP build.

## Parity with Android

- Same `AppTheme`, navigation, and i18n resources from `commonMain`.
- Haptics: wire `JourneyHaptics.ios.kt` when UIKit feedback is ready (Android already has light click).
- OAuth deeplink: same scheme `app.mymultiverse.kmp://auth/callback`.
- Push: APNs token upload parallels FCM on Android.

## Testing

- No iosInstrumentedTest in repo today — rely on unit tests + manual iOS smoke.
- After iosMain changes: compile iOS target before claiming done.

## Anti-patterns

- Android-only APIs in `commonMain` without expect/actual.
- Platform-specific strings outside `composeResources`.
- Duplicating nutrition/business logic in Swift.
